    "faq_8XYCd7": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question_kkQ9cg": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How does club identification work without sensors?",
            "text": "<p>Every insight Arccos provides — including Strokes Gained analytics, scoring breakdowns, and personalized recommendations on where to improve — is available without attaching sensors to your golf clubs.</p><p>For deeper club-level data, you have several options. AI-assisted tagging can infer which club you used based on shot distance, manual tagging allows you to enter club information yourself, and Smart Sensors can automatically track every club in your bag. All three options are completely optional and never required to get the full Arccos golf tracking experience.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_Xzd3JJ": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How is Arccos Air different from Arccos Smart Sensors?",
            "text": "<p>Both Arccos Air and Arccos Smart Sensors provide access to the same Arccos golf game tracking features and performance insights. The key difference is how your shots are tracked.</p><p>Arccos Air is a single wearable golf tracker that replaces the need for your phone, Apple Watch, or sensors attached to your clubs. Smart Sensors attach to each club and require you to carry your phone or use an Apple Watch during the round, but they automatically identify which club you hit on every shot.</p><p>You can also use Arccos Air together with Smart Sensors for a fully automatic, phone-free shot tracking experience.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_mBKjNB": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What’s included in the box?",
            "text": "<p>Arccos Air wearable, charging case, and a one-year Game Tracking subscription with full access to the Arccos golf app and all game tracking features. No sensors or additional accessories are required to start tracking your golf rounds.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_rXdYVi": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How many rounds of data do I need before I get useful insights?",
            "text": "<p>Just one round. After your first round of golf, Arccos provides a complete Strokes Gained breakdown, scoring insights, and Smart Club Distances.</p><p>As you play more rounds, your data becomes even more accurate and your performance trends become clearer — but you’ll start getting meaningful insights into your golf game from day one.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_73aEUt": {
          "type": "question",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "title": "Does Arccos Air work on Android?",
            "text": "<p>At launch, sensorless game tracking with Arccos Air requires an iPhone.</p><p>Android support is coming soon. In the meantime, Android users can pair Arccos Air with Arccos Smart Sensors to enable full golf shot tracking and performance insights.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
      },
